The article discusses the new guidance announced by the President regarding the nuclear weapons employment strategy of the United States. The President aims to align U.S. nuclear policies with the security environment of the 21st century and work towards achieving a world without nuclear weapons. The guidance emphasizes maintaining a credible deterrent, reducing the role of nuclear weapons in deterring non-nuclear attacks, and examining and reducing the role of launch under attack in contingency planning. It also focuses on strengthening non-nuclear capabilities and managing the nuclear weapons stockpile effectively. The President supports modernizing the nuclear enterprise and seeking negotiated cuts with Russia to move beyond Cold War nuclear postures. The strategy aims to maintain strategic stability with Russia and China, strengthen regional deterrence, and reassure U.S. allies and partners. The Department of Defense will begin updating and aligning its directives and contingency plans over the next year to implement this policy.